radiographic_examinations.findings: Multiple subcentimeter left axillary lymph nodes; mixed lytic and sclerotic lesions involving multiple vertebral bodies and the sternum.

Multiple hypodense lesions in the liver; enlarged kidneys with multiple bilateral hypodense lesions; a large abdominal mass measuring 10.8 cm by 8.3 cm by 12.2 cm; a small amount of ascites; retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy up to 2.5 cm in diameter; mottled lytic-sclerotic appearance of the skeleton without pathologic fractures.
Moderate radiotracer uptake in the abdominal mass, multiple lymph nodes, intense uptake in multiple bones.
